			<translation>
				One's mind must always remain completely untamable; one's genius especially illuminated;
				and one's body of the most agile kind. For this, one needs a meager diet, unceasing habit,
				and a continuously burning desire. No thirst more desirous of the innermost secrets, 
				no aspiration as vigorous for the world. No love or passion of humanity as eager or serious.
				Let one's industriousness spread out in like manner, and why not?
				After I have begun, should I stop when conquered?
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
